  "prompt": "How can you determine the chemical formula for iodine propanone?",
  "response": "To determine the chemical formula for iodine propanone, we need to understand its components and structure. Iodine propanone generally refers to an iodinated derivative of propanone (acetone). \n\nThe chemical formula for propanone (acetone) is \\( \\text{C}_3\\text{H}_6\\text{O} \\). Incorporating iodine into this structure leads to the formation of a compound known as iodoacetone or iodopropanone.\n\nIn iodoacetone, one of the hydrogen atoms in the methyl group of acetone is replaced by an iodine atom. Consequently, the chemical formula becomes \\( \\text{C}_3\\text{H}_5\\text{IO} \\).\n\nKeep in mind there can be different iodinated derivatives of propanone, so ensure this matches the context or variant (like mono-iodopropanone or poly-iodopropanone) you are looking for.",
